org.waarp.openr66.protocol.networkhandler

Class ClientNetworkChannels

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.waarp.openr66.protocol.networkhandler.ClientNetworkChannels

  • public class ClientNetworkChannels
extends Object
    Client NetworkChannelReference attached to one HostId. This class is used to keep information for one HostID when it connects as client to the current Host. As one Id can be shared or one can use direct send, so having a connection by request, this class is useful when one wants to know who is connected and how many times.
    Author:
    Frederic Bregier
